dmenu - dynamic menu
====================
dmenu is an efficient dynamic menu for X.


Requirements
------------
In order to build dmenu you need the Xlib header files.


Installation
------------
Edit config.mk to match your local setup (dmenu is installed into
the /usr/local namespace by default).

Afterwards enter the following command to build and install dmenu
(if necessary as root):

   make clean install is not recommended on Debian without changing the MakeFile
   
   symlinks are recommended. 
   
   sudo ln -sf /path/to/dmenu/dmenu /usr/local/bin
   sudo ln -sf /path/to/dmenu/dmenu_run /usr/local/bin
   sudo ln -sf /path/to/dmenu/dmenu_path /usr/local/bin
   sudo ln -sf /path/to/dmenu/stest /usr/local/bin
